Agreement

We can use a range of spoken expressions to show we agree with the speaker. 
Agreeing with an affirmative statement. 

I'm here for the interview. 
So am I./I am, too./Me, too.

I work in the city.
So do I./I do, too./Me, too./Same here.

I like the New York Yankees.
So does he./He does, too.

Agreeing with a negative statement:
I don't like the movie.
Neither do I./Nor do I./I don't either.

I don't like the New York Mets.
Neither does he./Nor does he./He doesn't either.
